    Awesome name for awesome pizza. Love coming here for many reasons:

    1. Delicious pizza. So far we've only bought pizza here by the slice. The slices alone gives you an idea of how good their entire pie will be. The crust is crispy yet chewy and the toppings are... *chef's kiss*... fresh and of quality. For by the slice, they have cheese, pepperoni and a rotating flavor available at $4-$5 for a generous piece. That should be enough of a reason to keep coming back.

    2. Excellent beer and wine selection. Seriously, top notch beers on draft and a wine list that made me go "wow you guys carry this?".

    3. Vibe. Its so laid back and casual. Not too midtown bougie. The staff is really friendly and keep the place and outdoor seating area looking clean.

    Because of all of thee above, Pizzasaurus Rex has been our go-to spot for our weekly midtown dates.

    Pepperoni slice

    The Spot: My first time at this place was on a Saturday and the place was quiet and empty--my kind of place! After I placed my order and found a comfortable spot out in their patio, the crowd started coming in. I enjoyed my beer at a pace and it was VERY relaxing. I am just glad to be able to hang outside again at local establishments as I love people watching--but mostly seeing people with their pets out and about.

    Pizza: I ordered the vegan cheese pizza. Quite honestly I had low expectations because vegan pizza is a hit or miss. Whooweee did they hit this one! The crust and the pizza sauce was perfecto! The crust was crunchy and hot and perfect temperature for biting without scalding the roof of your mouth. The Dino sauce was good--it was cilantro chutney and it paired well with the pizza. I wish they put more basil leaves because I LOVE basil but the pizza was great regardless.

    Price: pricing for this vegan cheese pizza is reasonable.

    Conclusion: I WILL DEFINITELY COME BACK!!

    Cutest pizza shop logo goes to this place! Such a memorable name too. Pizzasaurus Rex is the newest little addition to Midtown Sacramento!

    We were pretty hungry and driving from Elk Grove so we placed our order online on our drive over. It was ready by the time we arrived so it was perfect! We took our hot pizza and ate on their private outdoor patio. There are a few tables on the side patio but there are also some tables out in the front sidewalk too.

    We ordered a combo pizza, and then I wanted to try the dino slice of their daily special, which was a breakfast pizza with chicken apple sausage, salami, fennel, potato, egg and cheese. It was amazing!! They should make large sizes of that pizza, it would be perfect for weekend brunch time. The combo pizza was just as good though, especially with the dino sauce, which you can add on the side for 50 cents. It's a jalapeo cilantro sauce and that was the winning part of this meal for me! You don't even need to put a lot to get the flavor, so the little side of sauce was plenty for our whole combo pizza.

    I like the crust here, it's in between thin crust and thick crust. It wasn't oily either, and perfectly cooked. I wish they had more flavor combinations but I will definitely be back to try more of their rotating specials and dessert slice!

    The vegan pepperoni pizza is SO GOOD!!! I ordered a half sheet pizza for $26, and it served 4 people.this is definitely a 5-star pizza.

    The pickup procedure was less than ideal for the following reasons.
    1. They don't offer curbside pickup.
    2. They were running behind schedule by about 10 minutes so a lot of people were just waiting around.
    3. There's only one door to get inside to pick up your order, and if someone is standing at the counter ordering, you can't enter while maintaining social distancing.

    Despite all of that, I would still go back and risk my life for that pizza, because that's how delicious it is.

    Been following this place on Instagram, waiting for them to open since pizza is one of my favorite genres of food. There's a few pizza places in midtown but a new one is always welcome IMO.

    Ordered two pies online during their grand opening weekend. I showed up to pick it up at the tome the online ordering system said to, but it seems like there was an issue and the order didn't print in the back. They apologized and offered to pour me a beer while they made the pizzas. It was a very nice day that almost felt like spring despite it being January, so I didn't really mind the opportunity to sit on their patio. They have Revision Disco Ninja on tap which is a great beer. Their tap list was impressive and I'm excited to go back and try some more.

    I got home with the fresh pizza and dug in. Immediately I was impressed by the cheese. It pulled into strings, just like the classic pizza joints I enjoyed as a kid. The crust was pretty good- not too thick or crispy, I think it was a perfect medium. The ingredients all tasted fresh, I really enjoy mushroom on pizza and I think it was perfectly cooked. I think it was a great all around classic and fresh tasting pizza. My girl enjoyed the potato pizza, as she typically goes for white sauce pizzas. Will definitely visit again.

    A new pizza restaurant opened up 3 blocks from my house in midtown Sacramento. Intriguing yes?
    Then I read that it will have Vegan options. Now I am uber intrigued!
    We ordered the half sheet pepperoni on national pizza day. They were super busy! Well duh. National pizza day.
    They have a nice selection of beers and a very nice place inside. They sell slices from the side window on the little patio they have. The have a few tables for social distance dining out front as well.
    Website was easy to use. Pizza was $33 including 20% tip they definitely deserve. Side note if you aren't tipping on to go food during a pandemic you are a bad person.
    That young man who was working the front was HUSTLING! Practically running at some points. All while being super nice and helpful.
    Took it home because well you know pandemic and all. Hot out of the over! It was amazing! Perfect crust, savory sauce, not too much cheese (vegan cheese isn't designed to be used in excess. Trust me) and the pepperoni was the very best I have ever had. No red peppers or ranch required on this perfect pie. Just the right amount of spice.
    If I was Pizzasaurus I wouldn't tell anyone what brand they use. Keep em guessing and coming back. Folks have asked me and I was like just eat the pizza you cheap bastards.
    I would eat here every day if my waistline would permit!
    It's a blessing to have a great pizza place in my neighborhood!

    Vegan pepperoni half sheet

    I always cringe to review pizza because it's so subjective... everyone has their own tastes!

    That said, this wood fired thin crust had almost too much cheese. I liked it personally, but if you don't like chewy cheesy floppy pizza I recommend asking for light cheese. The pepperoni was classy with some arugula (I think?). It was good but I could have stood for it being a tiny bit crispier. The dough wasn't the most tasty I've had, but ok I guess. If I were to just review the pizza it would be 3 stars. To be fair - I only had one slice of pepperoni so maybe other stuff is better but I feel like crust is a key component and you can't save it with too much cheese.

    Beer selection is good, with a decent selection of taps and cans. They also have wine.

    It was dead as disco here on a Monday night, with the bars next door seated to capacity. The sweet waitress said they've been open for a month now, so I hope business picks up, but maybe when it's not a Monday night it'll be more hoppin. I don't judge based on that, since I prefer to scarf by my lonesome anyhow.

    Good seating and location.

    Customer service was superb. 5 stars for them!

    Not much to say. Great beer and service, but pizza was meh.

    This is a fantastic new place that just opened a few weeks ago. Located in the original location of Rick's Dessert diner, next door to the Gokden Bear, the restaurant has been fully remodeled and updated. They are serving craft beer, and wine in both for here and to go formats.

    The patio is small and set up perfectly. Staff is friendly and on point. Food is amazingly good, and the pizza is worth every penny. Highly recommend the green sauce, though beware it is spicy. The ranch sauce was perfect and exactly whT a great Ranch should taste like.

    A fantastic experience, and I recommend it for everyone. There are even truly amazing looking vegan options, so anyone can try it out. Remember to take home some beer when you leave.
